{
  "game_mode": "god",
  "user_id": "browser-test-1771316063",
  "selected_prompts": [],
  "use_default_world": false,
  "story_history": [
    {
      "text": "Character: A curious scholar seeking forgotten knowledge. | Setting: A quiet library filled with ancient tomes | Description: Browser test campaign",
      "mode": "god",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 1
    },
    {
      "text": "You pause to consider your options...",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 2
    },
    {
      "text": "Start Adventure",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 3
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Morning light filters through the high arched windows of the Athenaeum, catching dust motes that drift between towering bookshelves. The air smells of aged parchment, leather binding, and something faintly metallic\u2014ink, perhaps, or secrets kept too long. Rows of oak tables stretch across the grand reading hall, most occupied by hunched scholars muttering over crumbling codices.\n\nYou stand at the entrance, Aric, a fighter whose muscles are more suited to sword drills than scholarly pursuits. But the brain trusts what the heart craves, and your eye has been drawn to the restricted section\u2014a chain-link barrier separating the public archives from texts too dangerous for common eyes.\n\nA single librarian sits behind an ornate desk near the barrier: an elderly woman with silver-streaked hair pulled back in a severe bun, her nose buried in a ledger. She hasn't noticed you yet.",
      "sequence_id": 4,
      "actor": "gemini"
    },
    {
      "text": "Approach the Librarian - Speak with the elderly librarian about accessing restricted texts",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 5
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Midday (12:00:00) in the Athenaeum of Whispered Tomes\u2014you straighten your tunic and approach the elderly librarian's desk, your boots quiet against the worn stone floor.\n\nThe librarian looks up as you approach, pushing a pair of wire-rimmed spectacles up her narrow nose. Her eyes\u2014pale gray and sharp as flint\u2014assess you with the practiced scrutiny of someone who has spent decades judging the worthiness of scholars.\n\n\"Good afternoon,\" you say, keeping your voice respectful. \"I'm seeking access to the restricted section. Are there procedures I should follow?\"\n\nShe regards you for a long moment, her pen hovering over the open ledger. \"The restricted section is not for casual browsing.\" Her voice is dry, academic. \"These texts require special authorization from the Curatorium. Do you have a writ?\"\n\nYou hesitate. \"I don't, actually. Perhaps there's another way? I'm willing to prove my... dedication.\"\n\nOne silver eyebrow arches. \"Dedication?\" She sets down her pen. \"The Athenaeum has seen many seekers of 'forgotten knowledge,' young man. Most seek treasure maps or arcane secrets. What draws you specifically to our restricted archives?\"\n\nHer question hangs in the air\u2014genuinely curious, perhaps, but also testing. Behind her, the chain-link barrier separating the public hall from the restricted section gleams faintly in the afternoon light.",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 6
    },
    {
      "text": "Be Honest - Tell the librarian you&#x27;re searching for knowledge about an ancient threat\u2014the truth may resonate with a scholar&#x27;s curiosity",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 7
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Midday (12:05:00) in the Athenaeum of Whispered Tomes\u2014you take a breath, deciding that honesty might be the best currency with someone who has spent decades judging the worthiness of seekers.\n\n\"The truth,\" you say slowly, \"is that I've been having... dreams. Visions of something ancient stirring in the dark. Fragmented images\u2014a sealed door, runes that seem to writhe when I close my eyes, and a voice calling out in a language I don't recognize but somehow understand.\"\n\nYou pause, gauging her reaction. \"I don't know what it means. But these dreams started three weeks ago, and they're getting stronger. I came to the Athenaeum because if there's any record of such things\u2014any warning that was sealed away\u2014I'll find it.\"\n\nArchivist Thessa's expression shifts almost imperceptibly. The practiced neutrality falters, replaced by something that might be concern\u2014or perhaps recognition. She removes her spectacles, setting them carefully on the desk.\n\n\"Dreams, you say,\" she murmurs. \"What else have you seen?\" Her voice has dropped, become less formal. \"These visions\u2014do they follow any pattern? Specific symbols, perhaps? A color that recurs?\"",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 8
    },
    {
      "text": "Start Adventure",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 9
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Archivist Thessa's pale gray eyes fix on you, pen still hovering over the ledger. The question hangs in the air\u2014between the scent of old parchment and the faint creak of wooden beams. She's waiting for your answer.",
      "sequence_id": 10,
      "actor": "gemini"
    },
    {
      "text": "Look around and describe what you see.",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 11
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Midday (12:05:00) in the Athenaeum of Whispered Tomes\u2014your eyes drift away from Archivist Thessa's penetrating gaze to take in your surroundings.\n\nThe grand reading hall stretches before you, a cathedral of knowledge. Towering bookshelves of dark oak reach toward the vaulted ceiling, their iron rungs bearing countless tomes bound in faded leather, cracked vellum, and something that looks unsettlingly like scaled skin. High arched windows frame the exterior\u2014rolling hills and distant forest beyond, but the light they cast is thin and grey.\n\nRows of long oak tables fill the center of the hall, occupied by hunched scholars. A young man with ink-stained fingers copies from a crumbling codex nearby, his quill scratching furiously. Across the way, an elderly woman annotates margins of a massive star chart, muttering calculations to herself. Near the windows, a hooded figure pores over a text you can't see, their face shadowed beneath a cowl.\n\nThe air is thick with the scent of aged parchment, beeswax, and something faintly metallic\u2014old ink, perhaps, or secrets.\n\nTo your left, the public archives stretch onward, shelves disappearing into dim recesses. To your right, the chain-link barrier of the restricted section gleams faintly, its lock heavy and ancient.\n\nBehind the desk, Archivist Thessa watches you with those sharp grey eyes, waiting.",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 12
    }
  ],
