      "text": "Character: A curious scholar seeking forgotten knowledge. | Setting: A quiet library filled with ancient tomes | Description: Browser test campaign",
      "mode": "god",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 1
    },
    {
      "text": "[CHARACTER CREATION - Concept]\n\nYou've chosen to create a **curious scholar** seeking forgotten knowledge in a **quiet library filled with ancient tomes**.\n\n**CAMPAIGN SUMMARY**\n- **Title:** Browser Test Campaign\n- **Character:** Not specified yet\n- **Setting:** Library with ancient tomes\n- **Companions:** None\n\n---\n\nHow would you like to create your character?",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 2
    },
    {
      "text": "Start Adventure",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 3
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Morning light filters through stained glass windows, casting prismatic patterns across rows of towering bookshelves. Dust motes dance in the sunbeams as you step deeper into the Athenaeum\u2014the largest repository of forbidden knowledge in the realm. The air smells of aged parchment and candle wax.\n\nAncient tomes line the walls from floor to vaulted ceiling. Somewhere in this vast collection lies the *Codex of Eternal Echoes*, a text your mentor believed held secrets capable of reshaping the world. But the library is vast, and not all its contents wish to be found.\n\nA weathered librarian at the front desk glances up from her ledger. \"Seeker, are you?\" she rasps. \"The restricted archives lie through yonder door\u2014but be warned. Books have been going missing. And last week, a scholar who ventured into the deeper stacks was found wandering the halls, mind shattered, speaking of shadows that move when unobserved.\"",
      "sequence_id": 4,
      "actor": "gemini"
    },
    {
      "text": "Explore the Restricted Archives - Head through the door the librarian indicated to search for the Codex",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 5
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Morning (08:05:00) in the Restricted Archives\u2014you push through the heavy oak door into a corridor lit by flickering magical sconces. The air grows noticeably colder as you descend into the library's depths.\n\nThe restricted section differs markedly from the public areas. Bookshelves here are ancient\u2014dark wood older than the kingdom itself, their shelves carved with symbols you don't recognize. Dust lies thicker here, undisturbed for years. Your footsteps echo in the unnatural silence.\n\nRows of tomes stretch into shadowed darkness, their spines bearing titles in languages both familiar and alien. *Codex of Eternal Echoes*\u2014your mentor's words echo in your mind. But where? The archives sprawl endlessly before you.\n\nAs you venture deeper, you notice something: several empty spaces on the shelves, gaps where books should be. The missing texts the librarian mentioned. One such gap sits at eye level, the shelf beneath it scratched with three words etched into the wood: \"DON'T TRUST\u2014\"\n\nThe sentence trails off, unfinished.",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 6
    },
    {
      "text": "Examine the Empty Shelf - Investigate the gap where a book was removed, and the cryptic warning scratched below it",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 7
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "You kneel before the gap in the shelf, bringing your torch closer. The empty space is roughly the size of a medium tome, the dust around its edges disturbed\u2014as if the book was pulled recently. Running your fingers along the shelf beneath, you feel the rough grooves of the scratched warning: \"DON'T TRUST\u2014\"\n\nThe message simply stops, as if the writer was interrupted\u2014or ran out of room. You examine the surrounding books for context. The neighboring volumes are treatises on mind magic and dimensional theory. One spine catches your attention: \"The Psychic Shackles: A Study of Mental Binding Rituals.\"\n\nAs you reach for it, you notice something else. Faint scorch marks on the shelf's edge, and a smell\u2014barely detectable beneath the dust and aged parchment. Sulfur. The faintest hint of something infernal.\n\nThe missing book wasn't just removed. It was taken by force.",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 8
    },
    {
      "text": "Start Adventure",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 9
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Morning (08:05:00) in the Restricted Archives\u2014your eyes remain fixed on the unfinished warning etched into the shelf. \"DON'T TRUST\u2014\" The words cut off abruptly, as if whoever wrote it was interrupted... or feared completion.\n\nYou run a finger along the scratched letters, feeling the grooves deeper than casual scratching. This was deliberate. Someone wanted to leave a warning, but couldn't finish.\n\nNearby, your torch catches the edge of something half-hidden behind a neighboring tome\u2014a piece of parchment, yellowed with age, partially tucked between two leather-bound volumes. It bears a seal you don't recognize: a broken circle with an eye in its center.\n\nThe archives stretch into shadow ahead, but this corner holds secrets closer to the surface.",
      "sequence_id": 10,
      "actor": "gemini"
    },
    {
      "text": "Say hello in one short sentence.",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 11
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Invalid JSON response received. Please try again.",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 12
    }
  ],
