{
  "session_header": "[SESSION_HEADER]\nTimestamp: 1000 DR, Mirtul 12, 09:20:00\nLocation: The Athenaeum of Whispers - Grand Atrium\nStatus: Lvl 1 Fighter | HP: 12/12 | XP: 0/300 | Gold: 10gp",
  "resources": "HD: 1/1, Potions: None, Exhaustion: 0",
  "narrative": "Morning (09:20:00) in the Grand Atrium of The Athenaeum of Whispers‚Äîyou choose your next words carefully, weighing how much truth to share with the elderly librarian.\n\n\"I'm researching the Pre-Sundering cosmological theories,\" you say, allowing a hint of excitement to creep into your voice. \"Specifically, texts that discuss the nature of the Far Realm and its... influence on our reality. The Sundering didn't occur in a vacuum‚Äîthere are patterns, echoes of what came before.\"\n\nYou pause, studying Caelindis's reaction. \"The Depository holds texts from that era, doesn't it? Not the dangerous knowledge itself, but scholarly observations. The kind of thing a serious researcher would need to understand the full picture.\"\n\nCaelindis (Lvl 3) listens, her initial amusement fading into genuine interest. Her weathered hands cease their fidgeting with the scrolls.\n\n\"Pre-Sundering cosmography,\" she murmurs, more to herself than to you. \"That's... not a common pursuit. Most seekers these days want power, secrets to exploit.\" She looks at you anew, her pale eyes narrowing slightly. \"But you speak like someone who truly wishes to *understand*.\"\n\nShe sighs softly, glancing toward the locked iron door on the upper gallery. \"The Depository does contain what you seek‚Äîfragments of the Loremasters' observations, intercepted communications from the old empires, maps of a world that no longer exists.\" Her voice drops. \"But also darker things. Summaries of rituals best forgotten. Names that should not be spoken.\"\n\nCaelindis straightens, her expression becoming more guarded. \"I cannot grant access‚Äîonly the Council can. But...\" She hesitates, a flicker of something like memory passing across her face. \"If you were to petition them, a letter of endorsement from a recognized scholar would help considerably. There are a few who still hold enough standing.\"\n\nShe trails off, then adds quietly, \"The young man in the corner‚ÄîAldric‚Äîhis father sits on the Council. He's been researching here for months, ever more desperately. I wonder sometimes what he's looking for.\"",
  "planning_block": {
    "thinking": "Interesting‚ÄîCaelindis seems to have opened up more after my scholarly explanation. She's given me a lead: a connection to someone whose father is on the Council. I should probably investigate this Aldric, though he's clearly been here a while and might be competitive. She also mentioned 'darker things' in the Depository‚Äîdangerous rituals, forbidden names. This adds weight to the mystery.",
    "choices": {
      "inquire_about_alrdic": {
        "text": "Inquire About Aldric",
        "description": "Ask Caelindis more about the young man researching here whose father is on the Council",
        "risk_level": "low",
        "id": "inquire_about_alrdic"
      },
      "ask_about_endorsement": {
        "text": "Ask About Endorsement Process",
        "description": "Find out exactly what kind of scholar could endorse a petition to the Council",
        "risk_level": "low",
        "id": "ask_about_endorsement"
      },
      "probe_about_dark_knowledge": {
        "text": "Probe About Dark Knowledge",
        "description": "Ask Caelindis what she meant by 'darker things' in the Depository",
        "risk_level": "medium",
        "id": "probe_about_dark_knowledge"
      },
      "approach_alrdic": {
        "text": "Approach Aldric Directly",
        "description": "Leave the desk and introduce yourself to the cloaked figure in the corner",
        "risk_level": "medium",
        "id": "approach_alrdic"
      }
    }
  },
  "state_updates": {
    "world_data": {
      "world_time": {
        "hour": 9,
