    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Morning light filters through tall arched windows, casting long shadows across rows of towering bookshelves. The Athenaeum of Whispers lives up to its name\u2014the silence here feels ancient, broken only by the soft shuffle of pages and the occasional whisper of scholars bent over their research.\n\nYou stand in the Grand Atrium, a circular chamber of marble and mahogany where dust motes dance in the sunlight. Ancient tomes line the walls from floor to ceiling, some so old their spines have faded to illegibility. A few other patrons dot the reading alcoves\u2014mostly elderly scholars, a young apprentice copying texts, a cloaked figure in the corner reading something that makes them frown.\n\nThe head librarian, an elderly half-elf named Caelindis (Lvl 3), tends to a collection of scrolls behind the main desk. Her eyes lift to meet yours briefly, curious but not unfriendly.\n\nWhat draws your attention most is a locked iron door on the upper gallery\u2014a section you've never been permitted to access. A faded plaque above it reads: *RESTRICTED: The Forgotten Depository*.",
      "sequence_id": 4,
      "actor": "gemini"
    },
    {
      "text": "Approach Librarian Caelindis - Politely inquire about the restricted section and what it contains",
      "mode": "character",
