    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "The wind howls through the shattered dome overhead, carrying rain that lashes across your face like cold fingers. Lightning illuminates the ruins for a heartbeat\u2014that frozen moment when you can see everything: the collapsed eastern wall, the rusted telescope mount, the ancient star charts now barely visible on water-stained walls. Then darkness returns, and you stand alone at your post.\n\nThis observatory was once a place of wonder, they say. Scholars came from across the realm to gaze at the heavens. Now it's just another watchtower on the frontier, its purpose shifted from charting stars to watching for trouble.\n\nYou adjust your grip on your longsword, the leather wrapping on the hilt slick with moisture. The storm masks sounds\u2014the rustle of creatures in the brush, the approach of foes. But your eyes have adjusted to the dark, and you know these grounds better than any map.\n\nA flash of lightning. Was that... movement near the treeline? Or just the storm playing tricks?",
